真的有游戏把《瘟疫公司》反着抄了一遍……。
There was a real game to copy Plague Company...
栓子。
Thrombolts.
文化。
Culture.
每周98，疫情解药带回家？。
98 a week. Take home the antidote to the outbreak?
大家都知道，《瘟疫公司》前段时间在国内下架了，具体的来龙去脉我们之前已经讲过，这里就不再赘述。
As we all know, Plague Company got off the shelves in China some time ago. We've talked about it before, so we won't repeat it here.
。
.
当时你可能在社交平台上看过这样的玩笑：《瘟疫公司》想回来，估计得把玩法一百八十度翻转成《抗疫公司》，研究解药打败病毒才行。
You might have seen a joke on a social platform like this: Plague Company wants to come back, and it is estimated that it will have to be turned into Plague and that the antidote will defeat the virus.
。
.
而你要意识到，世界上的人分成两种，没商业头脑的和有商业头脑的。
And you have to realize that there are two kinds of people in the world, those who have no business sense and those who have business sense.
前者拿这句话当玩笑看的时候，后者早就开始了行动。
When the former took this remark as a joke, the latter began to act long ago.
。
.
于是，现在一款叫作《疫情解药》的游戏进入人们的视线。
As a result, now a game called "epidemic antidote" into people's eyes.
。
.
无论是从美术还是内容上，很容易就看得出来它基本就是一部大范围“借鉴”《瘟疫公司》的反转作品。
Whether from art or content, it is easy to see that it is basically a large-scale "borrowed" "Plague" inverted works.
《瘟疫公司》里玩家要传播病毒、升级病毒，那《疫情解药》里就改成研究解药、拯救世界。
"Plague" players to spread the virus, upgrade the virus, then the "epidemic antidote" to study the antidote, save the world.
。
.
当然，在这之前，你得先交98块钱，这是一个星期的订阅费用（现在打折了，只要28一周哦）。
Before that, of course, you have to pay $98, which is a week's subscription (now it's on sale for 28 weeks).
交了钱，你就能……成为更厉害的救世主！不交钱的话倒也没什么，就是那个“稍后提醒”的按钮藏在犄角旮旯里，自己慢慢找吧。
With the money, you can... be a better savior! If you don't pay, it's just that button "Remind me later" hides in a corner. Slowly search for it.
。
.
值得一提的是，《瘟疫公司》中不少人在意的“地图问题”，在这款“精神续作”中得到了修复——但仅限中国地区，其他地方依然进行了忠实的省略，甚至连阿拉斯加都划给了加拿大。
It is worth noting that the "Map Problem," which many people in Plague, was repaired in this "spiritual sequel" - but only in China, where it was faithfully omitted elsewhere, even to Canada.
。
.
不过和《瘟疫公司》不同，在《疫情解药》里你并没有选择病毒爆发在哪的权利，只能边看着病毒感染并杀死更多人，边坐等地图上冒出钞票的图标，把钱汇进你的银行户头。
Unlike Plague, however, you don't have the right to choose where the virus is going to explode, just watch the virus infect and kill more people, sit on a map and transfer the money to your bank account.
。
.
游戏中的资源不再是DNA点数，而是货真价实，以百万为单位的现金，而这些钱的用途，就是点击屏幕上那个硕大的“升级”，通过各种途径研发解药。
The resources in the game are no longer DNA points, but real, millions of dollars in cash, which is used to develop the antidote by clicking on the huge "upgrade" on the screen.
。
.
由于显而易见的点对点式“借鉴”，这款游戏在把“病毒变异”反转成“研发解药”的过程中出现了一些逻辑上的问题。
Because of the obvious peer-to-peer "learning," the game presents some logical problems in reversing the "virus mutation" into "developing an antidote."
比如在照搬传播途径这一栏的时候，复刻版的空气传播选项里，出现了“病原体不能在空气中存活很长时间”这种尴尬的说法——显然，这是文案连编都懒得编了。
For example, in copying the path of transmission, the awkward phrase "the pathogen cannot survive long in the air" appears in the carbon version of the air-borne option - apparently too lazy for a copybook.
。
.
看到这，您应该发现了：《疫情解药》这款游戏，做得实在不怎么样。
Seeing this, you should have found that the game "Epidemic Antidote" is really not doing very well.
。
.
而在这种低劣的制作水平下，这款游戏甚至产生了一些很黑色幽默的现象。
In this poor production level, the game even produced some very dark humor phenomenon.
。
.
举个例子，《疫情解药》里的病毒似乎极有政治觉悟，绝不出国传染，地图上《瘟疫公司》一样来回穿梭的飞机和轮船其实只是摆设。
For example, the virus in "The Antidote to the Epidemic" seems to be so politically aware that it never spreads abroad that the planes and ships shuttling back and forth like Plague on the map are really just furnishings.
我尝试的那一局里，病毒默认爆发在美国，就这样直到2023年，美国四分之一的人都已经死掉，全世界其他地方仍然没有一例感染。
In the first round I tried, the virus implicitly erupted in the United States, so that by 2023, one in four people in the United States would have died and there would still be no infections anywhere else in the world.
。
.
《瘟疫公司》里表示疫情的红色，变成了一堆蓝色的三角形。
In Plague, the red color of the epidemic turns into a blue triangle.
更神奇的是，都到这份儿上了，全人类依然保持着极高水平的克制，并且对美洲大陆上的惨剧一直袖手旁观，这其中甚至包括美国人自己。
Even more miraculously, all mankind, including even the Americans themselves, has maintained a high level of restraint and has stood idly by in the face of the tragedy on the American continent.
只有美国的国土上每隔几天蹦出来一个现金图标，点一下，加一百万块钱……而想研发一下疫苗，少说也得花三四千万。
Only a cash icon pops up every few days in the United States, click, add a million dollars... and to develop a vaccine would cost at least thirty or forty million dollars.
。
.
每天死个几万人，还就给这点儿拨款，美国人真沉得住气啊……。
Tens of thousands of people die every day, and that's the amount of money the Americans are spending...
顺带一提，《疫情解药》也还原了国家特征的设定（虽然没看出来有什么用），比如中国就是“温和的 湿润气候 富有 城市化 国家”，而美国……则是个“不富有 城市化 国家”。
Incidentally, The Epidemic Antidote also reverts to national identity settings (though it does not see much use), such as China, which is an "urbanized country with a mild humid climate," and the United States, which is... an "unurbanized country."
。
.
游戏如此神奇，我就还顺便查了一下它的神奇开发者，Action Portal。
So amazing was the game that I looked up its amazing developer, Action Portal.
。
.
他们在App Store上一共发布了三款作品，都是中文版，但也都无人问津且评价不佳。
They released three pieces on the App Store, all in Chinese, but none were taken seriously and rated poorly.
从《疫情解药》的说明中，可以顺藤摸瓜地找到它的官网，以及注册地址——俄罗斯的新西伯利亚市。
From the description of the "epidemic antidote," you can find its official website, as well as the registered address - Novosibirsk, Russia.
。
.
通过俄罗斯版的“天眼查”Rusprofile，可以很轻松地发现一个事实：。
With the Russian version of the "Skyeye" Rusfile, it's easy to see one fact:
这家公司既没有雇员，也几乎没有营业额。
The company has neither employees nor turnover.
而且这个Action Portal，和其他55家俄罗斯公司，统统属于同一个叫作诺维科夫的人，这些公司的注册地址，也全都是同一栋楼的不同房间。
And this Action Portal, along with 55 other Russian companies, belongs to the same people named Novakov and all have different rooms in the same building.
。
.
换句话讲，这不过是一个境外的壳而已。
In other words, it is just an offshore shell.
。
.
目前，《疫情解药》在App Store上的评分已经跌到了1.2分，从游戏质量来看，批评的内容也可想而知。
So far, the App Store score has fallen to 1.2, and the quality of the game suggests the criticism.
。
.
但和许多人指责的不同，《疫情解药》并不能完全算是《瘟疫公司》被下架后赶出来蹭红利的作品。
But, contrary to what many have accused, The Epidemic Antidote is not exactly the product of the Plague Company being pulled out of its shelves and receiving a bonus.
它其实二月初就已经上架了，这次之所以会引起大家的关注，主要是因为有人把它发到了社交媒体上，引起了一波共鸣。
It actually hit stores in early February, and this time it caught everyone's attention, mainly because it struck a chord with someone who sent it to social media.
。
.
不过……如果《瘟疫公司》还在的话，谁还会来玩它呢？。
But... if Plague is still in existence, who will play with it?
